== Herniotomy

=== Steps

1. Identification of hernial sac → Fish belly type appearance (dull white)  
2. Sac identified after incision in inguinal canal  
3. Sac lies anterolateral to spermatic cord with crescentic margin  
4. Isolate sac from spermatic cord up to deep inguinal ring  
5. Open sac  
6. Reduce contents to peritoneal cavity  
7. Transfix sac at level of deep inguinal ring  
8. Remove redundant part

*Contents:*  
- Omentocele (Omentum)  
- Enterocele (Gut)

== Herniorrhaphy

Strengthen posterior wall of inguinal canal and weak deep inguinal ring by approximating conjoint tendon with deep inguinal ring using *non-absorbable suture*.

*Types:*  
- Bassini (interrupted stitch)  
- Darning (continuous stitch)  
- Shouldice technique (4 layers)  
- Prolene mesh: non-absorbable (commonly used)